Czech Lottery Operator’s Debt Totals $2.43 Billion, CTK Says

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-05-10T11:57:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-10/czech-lottery-operator-s-debt-totals-2-43-billion-ctk-says.html
The total debt of Sazka AS, a
bankrupt Czech lottery operator, amounts to 41.1 billion koruna
($2.43 billion), according to claims registered at the municipal
court in  Prague ,  CTK  reported, citing Martina Lhotakova, the
court spokeswoman.  The validity of the claims has to be assessed by Sazka’s
bankruptcy administrator, Josef Cupka, the newswire said.  To contact the reporter on this story: Lenka Ponikelska in
Prague   lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  